      • findNameUsingIDOfSelfOrParent

        public Name findNameUsingIDOfSelfOrParent(RegistrationType type,
                                          String id)
        findName() variant that can cope with situations where the name we are looking for is of the form /A(a)/B(b)/C(<id>)/<type>
        Parameters:
        type - a registration type
        id - an ID
        Returns:
        the registered object's name, which is either the same as what findName(RegistrationType, String) returns, or which looks like /A(a)/B(b)/C(<id>)/<type>
